hopobject.body: What do you do? shop.thinkproducts.com This does suggest that the East Antarctic Ice Sheet may not be as stable in a warm climate as some models suggest, Hillenbrand says. And, given that it indicates that the Pliocene had both ice-free warm periods and glacial periods, it's an "interesting alternative scenario" to the more extreme reconstructions that suggest either widespread melting across East Antarctica or no melting at all relative to today.
